        "timestamp": "2017-11-27 21:42:46.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Michael,\n\n> Reviewing, but this JIRA was only created 6 min before the patch - I expect you have a lot of changes in the queue still?\n\nNo I create JIRA as I go, because I don't know what issue I'll find, so basically, I prepare the fix, then create the JIRA and submit the fix, because of the rule enforcing Issue-ID in commit msg (another fight, for another time).\n\n\n> Minor but don't you want your corporate email as the committer - I abandoned my old acm.org for example\n\nWell that's a personal note. I'd rather commit/participate in open source using my (upstream) gmail, as my afiliation to ONAP might not necessarly be coupled to my corporate affiliation. That happened to me in the past in other communities. That being said, it's pretty easy to update email address, so I might do it at some point, if the corporation wants to track this.\n\n> Looking to see if removing the logs for haproxy will affect anything else in the ELK stack\n\nWell, I'm running this, and things look fine. HAProxy message are really self-contained.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
